parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractors can cause the seat belts to remain extended, reducing their effectiveness in protecting occupants in the event of a crash, which can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belts fail to latch properly
the seat belts do not stay latched when brakes are applied
the shoulder belts will not retract
the seat belts remain extended and will not return to their original position
the seat belts fail to pull out of the housing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause overheating of transmission oil, which can lead to further damage and potentially start a fire.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or loses power
the transmission automatically shifts into neutral when coming to a stop
the transmission lurches or hesitates when shifting gears
the transmission oil is overheating
the transmission seal blows out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission overheating can cause damage to the transmission and other components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing the vehicle to lose power or stop suddenly.
symptoms: The transmission oil is overheating
the transmission oil is burning
the transmission is slipping or hesitating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission seal failure can cause transmission fluid to leak out, leading to damage to the transmission and other components.
symptoms: The transmission seal blows out
transmission fluid is leaking out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Dealership issues with transmission repair can cause delays and frustration for vehicle owners, potentially leaving them without a vehicle for an extended period.
